"url":"/synnick","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/090/657/36767bbaa150ba0e5f23d3edf1de6dc62eb41452_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"globaleaks","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1411023,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugInformative","message":"@edio the scrypt decrypt will not work in this context as the password_hash we have stored is not stored with scrypt_encrypt and is instead simply derived via the scrypt function. Since that function is non-reversible the suggestion to use scrypt.decrypt is inaccurate.\n\nClosing as informative.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-10T12:30:01.626Z","updated_at":"2017-01-10T12:30:01.626Z","actor":{"username":"synnick","cleared":false,"url":"/synnick","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/090/657/36767bbaa150ba0e5f23d3edf1de6dc62eb41452_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"globaleaks","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1411025,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::AgreedOnGoingPublic","message":"We would like to prevent duplicate requests in the future.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-10T12:31:22.525Z","updated_at":"2017-01-10T12:31:22.525Z","first_to_agree":true,"actor":{"username":"synnick","cleared":false,"url":"/synnick","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/090/657/36767bbaa150ba0e5f23d3edf1de6dc62eb41452_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"globaleaks","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1411082,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"I would like to take some time and review this again, before we disclose this report publicly. I understand your point concerning the `scrypt.decrypt()` function and I can see why this would not resolve this issue. Nevertheless, you can use the `hmac.compare_digest()` instead of the `==` operator, since removal of all the delays in place would make this operation susceptible to timing attacks.\n\nIn the mean time, I will try to create a working PoC to demonstrate the issue and I would highly recommend you look into the following articles/papers:\n\n- [A Lesson In Timing Attacks (or, Don‚Äôt use MessageDigest.isEquals)](https://codahale.com/a-lesson-in-timing-attacks/)\n- [Opportunities and Limits of Remote\nTiming Attacks](http://www.cs.rice.edu/~dwallach/pub/crosby-timing2009.pdf)\n- [Timing attack in Google Keyczar library](https://rdist.root.org/2009/05/28/timing-attack-in-google-keyczar-library/)","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-10T13:00:11.189Z","updated_at":"2017-01-10T13:00:11.189Z","actor":{"username":"edoverflow","cleared":true,"url":"/edoverflow","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/116/374/9a3cf4d62b2f507a0d33808aacbad863ec4455ac_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"globaleaks","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1411751,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugReopened","message":"Okay edio I am reopening this.\n\nIf you can demonstrate a timing attack we can award you with public recognition (bragging rights) and swag. Do not limit yourself to the login function.\n\nI am concerned that other attacks like side channels to disclose the creation of a new submission / the number of submissions / the size and number of files and so on may be vectors, but I have never been able to demonstrate the existence of such problems.\n\nHappy hunting!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-10T17:52:59.214Z","updated_at":"2017-01-10T17:52:59.214Z","actor":{"username":"synnick","cleared":false,"url":"/synnick","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/090/657/36767bbaa150ba0e5f23d3edf1de6dc62eb41452_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"globaleaks","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1424633,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"Any update @edio?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-17T11:29:17.109Z","updated_at":"2017-01-17T11:29:17.109Z","actor":{"username":"synnick","cleared":false,"url":"/synnick","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/090/657/36767bbaa150ba0e5f23d3edf1de6dc62eb41452_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"globaleaks","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1437802,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Sorry @synnick, I have been very busy the past two weeks and have not had the time to review this issue. I hope to get on to this as soon as possible and will report back.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-01-23T09:42:46.961Z","updated_at":"2017-01-23T09:42:46.961Z","actor":{"username":"edoverflow","cleared":true,"url":"/edoverflow","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https: